# Team workflow · Estilo de trabajo del equipo

|               |                                        |
| ------------- | -------------------------------------- |
| **Project**   | Henry's Top Notch — HVAC dashboard     |
| **Rule file** | `.cursor/rules/team-workflow.mdc`      |
| **Languages** | Español + English (both apply equally) |

---

## 0. AI — read first · IA — leer primero

|        |                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                          |
| ------ | -------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| **EN** | Before **any** change in this repo (code, refactor, components, data, styles, rules), the AI **must** read and follow this file. Verify every section below. Do not introduce patterns that break these rules. If the user request conflicts with this guide, explain it and align **before** editing.   |
| **ES** | Antes de **cualquier** cambio en este repo (código, refactor, componentes, data, estilos, reglas), la IA **debe** leer y aplicar este archivo. Comprobar todas las secciones. No introducir patrones que rompan estas reglas. Si lo pedido entra en conflicto, explicarlo y alinear **antes** de editar. |

**Checklist**

- [ ] Read `.cursor/rules/team-workflow.mdc`
- [ ] No hardcoded site copy in components
- [ ] Colors / overlay / type only via `@theme` in `globals.css`; components use `bg-*`, `text-*`, `ring-*` from tokens
- [ ] Shadows only via `@utility` in `globals.css` (`shadow-nav`, `shadow-panel`, …) — not `--shadow-*` in `@theme`, not long `box-shadow` in JSX
- [ ] Links use `text-body md:text-body-md lg:text-body-lg`; labels use `text-small md:… lg:…`
- [ ] Atomic design respected
- [ ] No unnecessary abstractions
- [ ] DOM: no extra wrappers only for `ref` / layout unless required (see §9)
- [ ] Layout: positioned containing block clear before `fixed` / portal / Context (see §9)

