## 6. Design tokens · Tokens en `globals.css`

All tokens live in `src/app/globals.css` (`@theme` + `@utility`). New values go there first — never arbitrary colors or shadows in components.

### 6.1 Colors · Colores

|        |                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                              |
| ------ | -------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| **EN** | Name `--color-*` after the **color** (`white`, `violet`, `rose`, `jet-black`), not UI roles (`primary`, `badge`, `accent`). If a name collides with Tailwind auto-utilities (e.g. `shadow-rose` vs pink badge), pick another **color name** or a clear variant — do not reuse a color token name for unrelated semantics. Use `bg-white`, `text-ink`, `bg-violet`, etc. — all must map to `@theme` tokens. **Forbidden in components:** `#hex`, `rgb`/`rgba`, `bg-[#…]`, raw Tailwind palette (`bg-gray-500`) unless added to `@theme` first. |
| **ES** | Nombrar `--color-*` por el **color** (`white`, `violet`, `rose`, `jet-black`), no por rol de UI (`primary`, `badge`, `accent`). Si choca con utilidades auto de Tailwind, otro nombre de color o variante clara. Usar `bg-white`, `text-ink`, etc. desde `@theme`. **Prohibido en componentes:** `#hex`, `rgb`/`rgba`, `bg-[#…]`, paleta Tailwind suelta sin token.                                                                                                                                                                           |

**Palette · Paleta:** `white`, `ink-black`, `violet`, `cornflower`, `steel`, `frost`, `ink`, `muted`, `dim`, `lilac`, `lilac-light`, `jet-black`, `rose`, `amber`, `forest`, `mint`.

### 6.2 Shadows · Sombras

|        |                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                   |
| ------ | ------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| **EN** | Shadows are **`@utility` classes** (Tailwind size + token color via `@apply`), **not** `--shadow-*` in `@theme`. Name by **UI surface type**, not by color alone. Do **not** use a utility name identical to `--color-*` alone (Tailwind may treat `shadow-{color}` as shadow **color** only — e.g. pink `shadow-rose` bug). Use the table below. |
| **ES** | Sombras como **`@utility`** (`@apply` con tamaño Tailwind + color del token), **no** `--shadow-*` en `@theme`. Nombrar por **tipo de superficie**, no solo por color. No usar utilidad con el mismo nombre que un `--color-*` aislado. Usar la tabla.                                                                                             |

| Utility · Utilidad | Use · Uso                                      |
| ------------------ | ---------------------------------------------- |
| `shadow-nav`       | Navbar, light elevation on thumbnails/badges   |
| `shadow-panel`     | Cards, hero block, section panels              |
| `shadow-flyout`    | Mobile menu dropdown panel                     |
| `shadow-control`   | Violet nav icons, menu button, active nav link |

### 6.3 Typography · Tipografía

|        |                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                      |
| ------ | -------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| **EN** | `--text-*` and `--leading-*` in `@theme`. Titles: `DashboardTitle` + `text-main-title` / `text-secondary-title` / `text-tertiary-title` + `leading-main-title` / `leading-secondary-title` / `leading-tertiary-title`. Body chain: `text-body md:text-body-md lg:text-body-lg` + `leading-body`. Small chain: `text-small md:text-small-md lg:text-small-lg` + `leading-small`. **Forbidden:** `text-[…]`, redefining Tailwind `text-sm`/`text-lg` in `@theme`. |
| **ES** | `--text-*` y `--leading-*` en `@theme`. Títulos: `DashboardTitle` + tokens de título. Body: `text-body md:text-body-md lg:text-body-lg`. Small: `text-small md:text-small-md lg:text-small-lg`. **Prohibido:** `text-[…]`, redefinir `text-sm`/`text-lg` de Tailwind en `@theme`.                                                                                                                                    |

### 6.4 Image overlay · Overlay de imagen

|        |                                                                                                                                                                       |
| ------ | --------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| **EN** | Single token: `bg-overlay` (`--background-image-overlay`), built from `--color-jet-black`. Use on photos via a `bg-overlay` layer. |
| **ES** | Un solo token: `bg-overlay`, derivado de `--color-jet-black`. En fotos con capa `bg-overlay`.                                      |

